60
00:05:11,352 --> 00:05:12,686
Are you here?

61
00:05:16,232 --> 00:05:17,650
Where are you?

62
00:05:17,691 --> 00:05:19,026
I'm in here.

63
00:05:21,278 --> 00:05:24,365
Sweetie, can you come in here
and sit down for a minute?

64
00:05:24,406 --> 00:05:26,158
I'll be there in one second.

65
00:05:29,954 --> 00:05:31,288
Hi.

66
00:05:31,330 --> 00:05:32,665
Sit down.

67
00:05:32,706 --> 00:05:34,291
You stand up.

68
00:05:35,418 --> 00:05:37,128
Sweetie, please sit down.

69
00:05:38,170 --> 00:05:39,588
And take your coat off.

70
00:05:39,588 --> 00:05:41,507
Maybe you should take it off.

71
00:05:46,429 --> 00:05:47,763
Well?

72
00:05:49,432 --> 00:05:51,517
I made a mistake.

73
00:05:53,436 --> 00:05:54,770
I'm sorry.

74
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:57,815
I made a mistake.

75
00:05:59,942 --> 00:06:02,319
You made what?

76
00:06:02,361 --> 00:06:05,614
If I could blink my eyes
and it would be a year from now...

77
00:06:07,032 --> 00:06:10,119
and we could be friends, best friends,
I would do it.

78
00:06:13,289 --> 00:06:15,624
We teach across the hall from each other.

79
00:06:16,792 --> 00:06:19,128
I'll see you all the time, every day.

80
00:06:21,297 --> 00:06:22,715
But listen, I want...

81
00:06:24,675 --> 00:06:27,762
-I want you to know something.
-Do you want?

82
00:06:27,803 --> 00:06:29,263
Yeah, thank you.

83
00:06:33,184 --> 00:06:35,227
What did you want me to know?

84
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:38,773
I'm 100 percent sure.

85
00:06:41,317 --> 00:06:43,986
Is it because I didn't say the right thing
the other night?

86
00:06:44,028 --> 00:06:46,989
-If you wanna pursue this drawing thing...
-It's nothing.

87
00:06:47,031 --> 00:06:49,158
-I just meant that if...
-I'm attracted to...

88
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:50,951
...somebody has to make some money.

89
00:06:50,993 --> 00:06:52,536
I don't...

90
00:06:52,578 --> 00:06:56,749
-I can't make love if we don't talk.
-I don't, I don't want this life!

91
00:07:03,005 --> 00:07:05,174
Don't you want to take your coat off?

92
00:07:07,885 --> 00:07:10,137
Why don't you want to take your coat off?

93
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:18,938
Oh, God!

94
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:53,681
I'm really sure we shouldn't...

95
00:09:14,762 --> 00:09:16,639
I'll see you in school.

96
00:09:27,817 --> 00:09:29,401
Come on.

97
00:10:24,165 --> 00:10:25,791
Can you explain this to me?

98
00:10:25,833 --> 00:10:29,378
Mrs. Epner Green, this is chaos.
Who's in charge?

99
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:32,715
-It says he has resigned.
-And you knew nothing about this?

100
00:10:32,757 --> 00:10:34,717
If Mr. Green is out,
why is there no substitute?

101
00:10:34,759 --> 00:10:36,260
Is he coming in?

102
00:10:36,302 --> 00:10:39,805
Mrs. Epner Green's class,
make space for Mr. Green's class.

103
00:10:39,847 --> 00:10:42,433
Mrs. Epner Green,
this is way too many kids for one room!

104
00:10:42,475 --> 00:10:44,477
Really, d'you think so?

105
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:47,980
-Well, Mrs. Epner Green
-Ms. Epner.

106
00:10:48,063 --> 00:10:52,693
OK, the parents can go.
Mr. Green will not be coming in.

107
00:10:52,735 --> 00:10:55,696
Ms. Epner will be teaching both classes.

108
00:10:55,738 --> 00:10:57,865
You don't know where he is?

109
00:10:59,533 --> 00:11:01,118
Have you slept?

110
00:11:04,246 --> 00:11:06,582
Don't do anything until you've slept.

111
00:11:06,624 --> 00:11:09,293
Don't think anything until you've slept.

112
00:11:10,628 --> 00:11:12,588
I have to drop her upstairs.

113
00:11:12,588 --> 00:11:15,591
It's gonna take me an hour to get a sub.

114
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:17,051
Love you.

115
00:11:18,052 --> 00:11:20,137
Can you watch them for five minutes?

116
00:11:20,179 --> 00:11:22,389
Go. Hurry back.

117
00:11:43,619 --> 00:11:45,496
Don't let anyone fix you up with anyone.

118
00:11:46,664 --> 00:11:50,251
A friend of mine set me up on a date,
I'm still recovering.

119
00:11:50,292 --> 00:11:53,796
Are you... coming on to me?

120
00:11:55,256 --> 00:11:57,091
What?

121
00:11:57,133 --> 00:11:59,009
My husband left me nine hours ago.

122
00:11:59,051 --> 00:12:02,138
Do you think you could control yourself
for five minutes?

123
00:12:05,307 --> 00:12:06,892
You betcha.

124
00:12:11,981 --> 00:12:13,649
Oh, my God!

125
00:12:13,691 --> 00:12:18,654
OK. You should come in.
This is bad timing

126
00:12:18,696 --> 00:12:20,906
-Do you know how old I am?
-Yes, I do.

127
00:12:20,948 --> 00:12:22,908
I want a baby. I can't explain it.

128
00:12:22,992 --> 00:12:26,620
It's like being hungry or having to pee.
Please don't tell me to adopt.

129
00:12:26,662 --> 00:12:29,290
I wouldn't. I won't. I never will.

130
00:12:33,669 --> 00:12:37,882
A 65-year-old lady in the Bronx
just gave birth to twins.

131
00:12:37,923 --> 00:12:41,135
-So... I mean, not that that's...
-Thanks.

132
00:12:41,177 --> 00:12:43,679
-Should I come in?
-Yes, you should come in. I just need...

133
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:45,389
Hi, I'm here.

134
00:12:46,182 --> 00:12:47,558
Sorry.

135
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:50,311
I heard your story. That's just horrible.

136
00:12:51,896 --> 00:12:54,148
Thanks.

137
00:12:54,190 --> 00:12:56,734
-I'm gonna go.
-April, don't go home alone.

138
00:12:56,776 --> 00:12:58,736
It's fine. I need to sleep.

139
00:12:59,737 --> 00:13:01,822
It's not gonna get any worse than this.

140
00:13:01,864 --> 00:13:06,243
<i>God, abounding in Mercy
Who dwells in the realms of the High</i>

141
00:13:06,285 --> 00:13:11,540
<i>Bring forth true repose
Under the wings of the Divine Presence</i>

142
00:13:11,582 --> 00:13:13,501
<i>in the great heights
of the holy and pure,</i>

143
00:13:13,542 --> 00:13:16,545
<i>who like the brilliance
of the heavens give shine</i>

144
00:13:16,545 --> 00:13:19,256
<i>to the spirit of
Gittel daughter of Tuvia and Hannah...</i>

145
00:13:19,590 --> 00:13:23,302
<i>who is deceased.
May her soul rest in Heaven</i>

146
00:13:23,469 --> 00:13:27,765
To Gertrude Trudy Epner,
who has gone to her lasting rest.

147
00:13:27,807 --> 00:13:29,809
Master of all, we pray to You,

148
00:13:29,892 --> 00:13:34,939
remember her worthy and righteous deeds
while among the living and say amein.

149
00:13:34,980 --> 00:13:36,774
Amein.

150
00:14:03,592 --> 00:14:04,885
Pardon me.

151
00:14:05,594 --> 00:14:08,639
Who does the, uh,
purchasing for the school?

152
00:14:08,681 --> 00:14:10,057
I'm sorry?

153
00:14:10,099 --> 00:14:13,352
Not the purchasing, the requisitioning.

154
00:14:13,394 --> 00:14:14,812
The office is that way.

155
00:14:14,854 --> 00:14:16,188
Thank you.

156
00:14:22,528 --> 00:14:24,905
-Are you April Epner?
-Can I help you?

157
00:14:25,948 --> 00:14:28,659
I represent someone from your past.

158
00:14:28,701 --> 00:14:31,996
Someone from your past
who's looking to make contact.

159
00:14:33,539 --> 00:14:38,043
Would the discovery of the identity
of your birth mother be welcome news?

160
00:14:39,044 --> 00:14:41,172
I'm her assistant and friend.
She's a celebrity.

161
00:14:41,213 --> 00:14:43,716
What kind of celebrity?

162
00:14:43,799 --> 00:14:47,094
She's, she's well known.
She really wants to meet you,

163
00:14:47,136 --> 00:14:49,305
but she's very cautious, you understand.

164
00:14:49,346 --> 00:14:51,432
But now I can definitely recommend it.

165
00:14:51,474 --> 00:14:53,434
You're recommending me?

166
00:14:53,434 --> 00:14:55,728
You taking this the wrong way?

167
00:14:55,770 --> 00:14:57,104
Here.

168
00:14:58,481 --> 00:15:00,649
Let her speak for herself.

169
00:15:36,519 --> 00:15:38,312
<i>" Dear Gabrielle,</i>

170
00:15:38,354 --> 00:15:41,023
<i>" Did you know Gabrielle
is what I named you?</i>

171
00:15:41,065 --> 00:15:44,235
<i>" I believe the time has come
for us to meet.</i>

172
00:15:44,276 --> 00:15:51,158
<i>" Let's have lunch tomorrow, Saturday,
you and me. Barbetta Restaurant at one.</i>

173
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:54,286
<i>"Your mother, Bernice. "</i>

174
00:15:55,788 --> 00:15:58,791
<i>Good afternoon.
Can I help you, miss?</i>

175
00:15:58,833 --> 00:16:03,462
Oh, hello. Do you happen to have
a reservation for someone named Bernice?

176
00:16:03,504 --> 00:16:07,675
<i>Yes, of course we do.
Right this way, please.</i>

177
00:16:10,428 --> 00:16:12,430
A glass of champagne while you wait?

178
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:17,560
Do you have a ladies room?

179
00:16:25,484 --> 00:16:27,319
<i>-Hello, beautiful.
-Oh!</i>

180
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:29,655
Thank you.

181
00:16:40,708 --> 00:16:42,668
I'm a... teacher.

182
00:16:50,718 --> 00:16:55,139
...sounds like Judy Holliday.
You get anyone besides her, hang up.

183
00:16:55,181 --> 00:16:57,808
You won't get in
unless you use my name, right?

184
00:16:57,850 --> 00:17:00,644
I know, it's terrible,
but we're talking about your health.

185
00:17:00,686 --> 00:17:02,313
<i>-Thank you very much.
-Mm.</i>

186
00:17:13,991 --> 00:17:15,451
Let me just look at you.

187
00:17:24,126 --> 00:17:26,587
-You're magnificent!
-What's your name?

188
00:17:26,587 --> 00:17:29,090
Oh, thank you.
Um, what is your name?

189
00:17:29,090 --> 00:17:30,966
-You got my letter.
-Uh, your last name?

190
00:17:31,008 --> 00:17:33,260
Oh, Graves.
I'm so happy you don't know it.

191
00:17:33,302 --> 00:17:35,971
-Why would I...
-How do you feel right now?

192
00:17:36,013 --> 00:17:37,348
How do you feel?

193
00:17:37,389 --> 00:17:42,144
I feel like you are the reward for
everything I ever did right in my entire life.

194
00:17:42,978 --> 00:17:45,356
-Oh!
-And how do you feel?

195
00:17:46,190 --> 00:17:48,317
I, um... Thank you.

196
00:17:48,359 --> 00:17:51,403
I'm wondering how you can be certain
you're actually my mother.

197
00:17:51,445 --> 00:17:54,907
Are you married?
I mean, do you have anyone?

198
00:17:54,949 --> 00:17:58,452
Someone who takes you in his arms
or her arms.

199
00:17:58,494 --> 00:18:00,287
God knows
I only want you to be happy.

200
00:18:00,287 --> 00:18:01,914
Someone who holds you in the night?

201
00:18:01,956 --> 00:18:03,791
-You didn't answer...
-Doesn't matter.

202
00:18:03,833 --> 00:18:07,169
Some of the richest periods of my life
came when I was between love affairs.

203
00:18:07,211 --> 00:18:09,964
-Were you raised with brothers or sisters?
-I have a brother.

204
00:18:09,964 --> 00:18:11,632
Oh, I wanna meet him.

205
00:18:11,674 --> 00:18:13,467
-It's a little soon...
-Hello, you two.

206
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:16,846
-Oh, Alan, you remember Gabrielle.
-It's April.

207
00:18:16,887 --> 00:18:19,765
Recovering from the abominable way
I approached you?

208
00:18:19,807 --> 00:18:23,185
I make for you a special
mother/daughter antipasto.

209
00:18:23,227 --> 00:18:25,855
Someday I'll tell you
how we have Alan to thank for this.

210
00:18:25,896 --> 00:18:27,940
I uh, I produced the show that led to this.

211
00:18:27,982 --> 00:18:31,652
I looked in the camera and
the whole story just came out. Our story.

212
00:18:31,694 --> 00:18:35,072
-Such a powerful moment.
-Excuse me, what is our story?

213
00:18:35,114 --> 00:18:37,074
-I'm sorry to bother you.
-That's all right.

214
00:18:37,116 --> 00:18:39,869
-Alan, do you have a pen?
-No, I just want to say, I love you.

215
00:18:39,910 --> 00:18:41,287
I watch you all the time.

216
00:18:41,328 --> 00:18:43,956
I think you're just the best.
Enjoy your lunch.

217
00:18:43,998 --> 00:18:45,332
Thank you.

218
00:18:45,374 --> 00:18:47,835
If you have a TV show,
why have I never heard of you?

219
00:18:47,835 --> 00:18:49,837
You watch local TV
at 10:30 in the morning?

220
00:18:49,837 --> 00:18:51,630
-Never.
-Me, either.

221
00:18:51,672 --> 00:18:53,758
How much do you know about
my parents?

222
00:18:53,799 --> 00:18:55,926
I know that you lost Trudy
three weeks ago,

223
00:18:55,968 --> 00:18:58,179
and you lost Julius
three years before that.

224
00:18:58,220 --> 00:19:01,223
-How do you know who they were?
-Oh, I've known since the day I lost you.

225
00:19:01,265 --> 00:19:02,850
-Were they good to you?
-How?

226
00:19:02,892 --> 00:19:04,977
-You weren't allowed to know that.
-I read it.

227
00:19:05,019 --> 00:19:07,938
Upside down,
across the adoption counsellor's desk.

228
00:19:07,980 --> 00:19:10,149
"Baby Girl Epner, born April first. "

229
00:19:10,191 --> 00:19:11,650
So, it's possible.

230
00:19:11,692 --> 00:19:13,736
-What?
-That you are who you say you are.

231
00:19:13,778 --> 00:19:15,821
Listen, I only got to have you
for three days,

232
00:19:15,863 --> 00:19:18,616
but that doesn't change the fact
that you are my daughter.

233
00:19:18,657 --> 00:19:21,118
You are the most important thing on earth
to me.

234
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:23,537
You must know that.
Do you have children?

235
00:19:23,537 --> 00:19:27,291
I think your own family might feel strange
about you tracking me down like this.

236
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:29,502
My family is me and you.

